    {
      "id": "89c1148fd8b99e09bb72ff75407ebf5748224ade",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-05 14:50:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWe would really like to keep 8.4 for a while longer.\n\nAlso are there plans to drop the el7.x series?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f4c4b001cbd7c042e5cb95842c0b220d1970be69",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-07 17:39:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nPing Shaun.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2658101e1d1d6a3be63e9ea2d79035965882ab98",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-07 17:43:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> We would really like to keep 8.4 for a while longer.\n\nSorry, didn't see this comment.  I didn't think this would still be in use at this point. The main question is whether this distro will be in use for 2.16.0+ and not whether it is in use for 2.15?\n\nI'm not totally against keeping it if it is still needed, but wanted to confirm that this older distro will actually be used for 2.16, or at least testing of master before 2.16 is released?\n\n > Also are there plans to drop the el7.x series?\n\nThat is the same issue - el7.9 is still in use by Oleg to do some types of regression testing, so my patch removes el7.8- but not el7.9.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1fd758d4a6eee574e4dd007a83d899cc9c9208c7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-08 00:41:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > We would really like to keep 8.4 for a while longer.\n> \n> Sorry, didn't see this comment.  I didn't think this would still be in use at this point. The main question is whether this distro will be in use for 2.16.0+ and not whether it is in use for 2.15?\n> \n> I'm not totally against keeping it if it is still needed, but wanted to confirm that this older distro will actually be used for 2.16, or at least testing of master before 2.16 is released?\n> \n>  > Also are there plans to drop the el7.x series?\n> \n> That is the same issue - el7.9 is still in use by Oleg to do some types of regression testing, so my patch removes el7.8- but not el7.9.\n\nYes, we will be using el8.4 for testing 2.16/master.\nEven when we get onto el9.x I suspect there will still be some overlap with older hardware having issues getting to the newer release.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "627e546fba509c610d17519e41494e8b7cb161ed",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-03-08 00:47:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nInteresting that this patch is left homeless:\n  ldiskfs/kernel_patches/patches/base/ext4-reset-exts-for-gcc10.patch\n\nAlso the kernel patches as well as:\n   config/lustre-build-ldiskfs.m4:36:\t83)     LDISKFS_SERIES=\"4.18-rhel8.3.series\"    ;;\nought to be dropped.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
